1287
01:21:03,312 --> 01:21:06,790


1288
01:21:06,790 --> 01:21:08,570
What we do now is the following.

1289
01:21:08,570 --> 01:21:11,380
We want to prove a
theorem that says

1290
01:21:11,380 --> 01:21:17,320
that if a sum r is 0 all
the way up to n, then,

1291
01:21:17,320 --> 01:21:20,520
if you take the product of the
following binomial coefficients

1292
01:21:20,520 --> 01:21:26,370
n choose r times 2n
choose n minus r,

1293
01:21:26,370 --> 01:21:30,460
this is equal to 3n choose n.

1294
01:21:30,460 --> 01:21:32,670
We need to prove this.

1295
01:21:32,670 --> 01:21:34,950
So we need to find
the proper set.

1296
01:21:34,950 --> 01:21:36,249
So how can we think about it?

1297
01:21:36,249 --> 01:21:37,790
Well, the idea is
that we're probably

1298
01:21:37,790 --> 01:21:43,020
going to choose n elements
out of 3n elements.

1299
01:21:43,020 --> 01:21:45,620
We're going to do
it in a special way.

1300
01:21:45,620 --> 01:21:50,890
And so the proof
will be as follows.

1301
01:21:50,890 --> 01:22:05,050
We take S to be all the
subsets of n balls chosen

1302
01:22:05,050 --> 01:22:19,990
from a basket of n red
balls and 2n green balls.

1303
01:22:19,990 --> 01:22:22,540
And this will do the trick.

1304
01:22:22,540 --> 01:22:25,310
So how do we do this?

1305
01:22:25,310 --> 01:22:32,690
We're going to first choose
the red balls and then

1306
01:22:32,690 --> 01:22:35,110
the green balls.

1307
01:22:35,110 --> 01:22:40,360
So let's first count S
in the very easy way.

1308
01:22:40,360 --> 01:22:44,570
Well, I just choose n balls
out of a basket of 3n balls.

1309
01:22:44,570 --> 01:22:47,100
I don't care how many
green or red balls I have.

1310
01:22:47,100 --> 01:22:51,465
So I have really 3n
choose n choices.

1311
01:22:51,465 --> 01:22:53,990


1312
01:22:53,990 --> 01:23:09,660
This is the number of n element
subsets from a 3n element set.

1313
01:23:09,660 --> 01:23:10,507
So that's easy.

1314
01:23:10,507 --> 01:23:14,710


1315
01:23:14,710 --> 01:23:16,860
Now, we can also count
it in a different way.

1316
01:23:16,860 --> 01:23:22,480
We first of all wonder
about the number of subsets

1317
01:23:22,480 --> 01:23:26,430
with exactly r red balls.

1318
01:23:26,430 --> 01:23:28,710
So how many are there?

1319
01:23:28,710 --> 01:23:32,220
Well, we choose r red balls
so we have n red balls.

1320
01:23:32,220 --> 01:23:35,760
So we need to choose
r out of those.

1321
01:23:35,760 --> 01:23:38,690
Now, in total, I need
to choose n balls.

1322
01:23:38,690 --> 01:23:41,700
So I still need to choose
n minus r balls out

1323
01:23:41,700 --> 01:23:43,830
of the set of green balls.

1324
01:23:43,830 --> 01:23:46,950
I have 2n green balls.

1325
01:23:46,950 --> 01:23:50,630
I'm going to choose n minus
r green balls over here.

1326
01:23:50,630 --> 01:23:55,130
So these are the red balls
that I select and here

1327
01:23:55,130 --> 01:23:57,420
are the green balls.

1328
01:23:57,420 --> 01:23:59,500
Now we'll use the sum rule.

1329
01:23:59,500 --> 01:24:01,760
And I add all the
different possible subsets

1330
01:24:01,760 --> 01:24:05,310
with 0 red balls, with
1 red ball, 2 red balls,

1331
01:24:05,310 --> 01:24:07,960
all the way up to n red balls.

1332
01:24:07,960 --> 01:24:19,360
So essentially, I get the
sum by the sum rule of r 0

1333
01:24:19,360 --> 01:24:25,330
all the way up to n where I
count the number of subsets

1334
01:24:25,330 --> 01:24:27,730
with exactly r red balls.

1335
01:24:27,730 --> 01:24:31,110
So that means I can choose
r out of the n red balls

1336
01:24:31,110 --> 01:24:37,190
and another n minus r out of
the 2n balls-- 2n green balls.

1337
01:24:37,190 --> 01:24:39,360
So now we equate
those two together

1338
01:24:39,360 --> 01:24:41,430
and that proves the theorem.

1339
01:24:41,430 --> 01:24:45,710
So the really hard part
in this type of proofs

1340
01:24:45,710 --> 01:24:51,130
is that you need some creativity
to find and define that set S

1341
01:24:51,130 --> 01:24:53,020
and see how that would work.

1342
01:24:53,020 --> 01:24:56,230
And the way to do that usually
is to look at this equation

1343
01:24:56,230 --> 01:24:58,390
